        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 30 at 3:57PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 357 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Raymond, or 36 miles southwest of Fort Collins, moving southeast at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree branches and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southwestern Boulder, Jamestown, Summerville, Wallstreet, Gold
Hill, Salina, Sunshine, Crisman, Raymond, Peaceful Valley,
Allenspark, Eldorado Springs and Riverside.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
